        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Heterotopic Pancreas: Histopathologic Features, Imaging Findings, and Complications" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Maryam  Rezvani" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Christine  Menias" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Kumaresan  Sandrasegaran" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Jeffrey D.  Olpin" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Khaled M.  Elsayes" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Akram M.  Shaaban" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="The authors review the imaging appearances, histopathologic features, and complications of heterotopic pancreas." /><meta name="Description" content="The authors review the imaging appearances, histopathologic features, and complications of heterotopic pancreas." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="Heterotopic pancreas is a congenital anomaly in which pancreatic tissue is anatomically separate from the main gland. The most common locations of this displacement include the upper gastrointestin..." /><meta name="Description" content="Heterotopic pancreas is a congenital anomaly in which pancreatic tissue is anatomically separate from the main gland. The most common locations of this displacement include the upper gastrointestin..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content="Radiological Society of North America" /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2017-03-13" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="manuscript" content="160091" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="doi" content="10.1148/rg.2017160091" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="url" content="http://dx.doi.org/10.1148/rg.2017160091" /><meta name="dc.Source" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.2017160091" /><meta name="dc.Language" content="EN" /><meta name="dc.Coverage" content="world" /><meta name="dc.